{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d6589675-c182-4d48-bae3-0890f934f85b","content":"PID 12345 doesn't exist on this machine. Here's how to diagnose and configure on the box where it's running:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Determine the runtime\n\n```bash\n# Check if CoreCLR libraries are loaded (CoreCLR = yes, NativeAOT = no)\ngrep -qE 'libcoreclr|libclrjit' /proc/<PID>/maps && echo \"CoreCLR\" || echo \"NativeAOT\"\n\n# Alternative: check if the binary is self-contained AOT\nreadelf -p .comment /proc/<PID>/exe 2>/dev/null | grep -i aot\n```\n\n**CoreCLR** processes load `libcoreclr.so` and `libclrjit.so`. **NativeAOT** binaries are statically compiled — no CLR libraries in memory.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Configure crash dumps\n\n#### For CoreCLR:\n\n```bash\n# Environment variables (set before launching the app)\nexport DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1\nexport DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4          # 1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full\nexport DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName=/tmp/dumps/coredump.%p.%t\nmkdir -p /tmp/dumps\n```\n\n#### For NativeAOT (uses OS-level core dumps):\n\n```bash\n# Enable core dumps via kernel\nulimit -c unlimited\necho \"/tmp/dumps/core.%e.%p.%t\" | sudo tee /proc/sys/kernel/core_pattern\nmkdir -p /tmp/dumps\n\n# Optional: install createdump for richer dumps if available\n# NativeAOT doesn't have the DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump hooks\n```\n\n#### For either runtime (systemd-coredump, recommended for production):\n\n```bash\n# Check if systemd-coredump is active\ncat /proc/sys/kernel/core_pattern\n# If it shows \"|/lib/systemd/systemd-coredump ...\", dumps go to /var/lib/systemd/coredump/\n# View them with: coredumpctl list\n```\n\n---\n\n### Quick summary\n\n| | CoreCLR | NativeAOT |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Detection** | `libcoreclr.so` in `/proc/PID/maps` | No CLR libs loaded |\n| **Dump mechanism** | `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump` env vars | OS core dumps (`ulimit -c`) |\n| **Analysis tool** | `dotnet-dump analyze` | `lldb` / `gdb` |\n\nRun the detection command on your target machine and I can help you with the exact config.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5ae27299-c5dd-4dbe-a38c-4c174ffe1624","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The process doesn't exist (PID 12345 is likely just a placeholder). Let me provide the user with guidance on how to determine the runtime and configure dumps, since I can't inspect the actual process.","outputTokens":730},"id":"f99f0f9b-b4b2-490c-98da-804399dd4dde","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:04:41.150Z","parentId":"4e616ff5-e011-410a-8cf2-5f4034395ef6"}
